rComments: The material was not hard in this course, because it is an introductory course afterall. It's just easy to underestimate the amount of practice needed  cause you have to be able to combine the theory and math together. He bell curved by 15-20% for us and the avg was still only a C. Do past exams, they are key.

Although I found Micro Econ to be extremely boring, I really liked Prof Cleveland. There's only one midterm now, but all multiple choice which is extremely difficult, one little mistake and then you get the entire question wrong. Cleveland was always helpful and I'm sad, but happy for him that he's retiring. All the best to him.
teacherRatingTags: ['Tough grader', 'Gives good feedback', "Skip class? You won't pass."]

rComments: Even though the class is offered through a web option, don't. Economics is NOT something you can idly watch on your laptop while listening to Cleveland. The material is harder on the test than what's covered in lectures, but the tutorials fill in the gaps. He also gave us a multitude of old tests which were very helpful.

I never got to know him, but i can say this course was super hard. The format of the tests was absurd
